Enjoy Luxurious Comfort with Total Control

				The dual massage will soothe you as you rest, and help you ease tension in your body after a long day, while customizable positions ensure you get the rejuvenating environment you desire for any bedroom activity. Enhanced safety features make this luxurious adjustable base a great addition for your home.
			

				The S-Cape's Wallhugger technology makes any comfort adjustment a smooth transition. Simplistic in design without sacrificing in function, you can even put yourself in a position of virtual weightlessness, taking pressure off of your lower back and limbs. Any way you like it is yours as you escape the cares of your day.
			






				Fabulous features to enjoy maximum comfort in bed
			






Wireless, Stand-Up Remote Control
The technologically advanced wireless remote control stands on its own, so you can place it on your nightstand for easy access.




Upholstery

							Our S-Cape adjustable base is upholstered in a gorgeous  
							contemporary gray patterned fabric, making it a great 
							neutral to fit any decor.
						










Dual Massage With On-Off Button
The dual massage, built into the adjustable bed base, means that there are two separate areas at work to soothe you. One loosens up your shoulders and one helps to unburden those hard-working legs. With the touch of a button, you'll get an awesome sensation of all-over relaxation.




Wallhugger® Engineering

							Leggett & Platt's innovation team developed 
							state-of-the-art technology that puts you at the center of  
							the bed's motion. While other adjustable bed bases lift  
							your upper body away from the wall - and away from your  
							nightstand - bases with Wallhugger® engineering lift you  
							up while simultaneously gliding you back. That means your  
							favorite book and the remote control are within reach  
							whenever you're ready for them
						









					S-Cape Remote Control
				




						Compare All Adjustable Beds
					




					Available Sizes
				






						*Does not include height of mattress
					


						The S-Cape comes 
						with 4" legs with 
						locking casters, giving the 
						base a height of 16"
					






						The 2 ½" locking leg casters can be used by themselves to give the base a height of 12". 
					

						The 4" legs can be used by themselves to give the base a height of 13 ½".
					

						The 4" legs can be used with the 2 ½" locking casters to give the base a height of 16".
					




					Adjustable Bed Protection
				



							Manufacturer's Limited Warranty
						

							The S-Cape comes with a manufacturer's warranty that includes 
							the following coverage:
							
1-Year Full Warranty 
2nd & 3rd Year Limited Warranty 
4th to the End of the 20th Year Limited Warranty  





					Extended 10 Year Adjustable Bed Warranty
				



							The Extended 10 Year Adjustable Bed Warranty extends the limited warranty and adds coverage not included in the limited warranty, including Repair and Replacement Protection for:
						

Motors 
Mechanisms (inclining, reclining, heating and vibrating) 
Electrical components (including motors and wiring) 
Controllers 
Power Surges 


							The Extended Warranty also comes with an industry-beating No Lemon Guarantee, as well as telephone support and a strong network of professional service technicians to conduct repairs.
						

							Plans are underwritten by an "A" rated insurance carrier.
						

							* Warranty not available in the state of Washington.
						



					How Does the Plan Work? 
				




								Year
							

								Problem
							

								Manufacturer's Limited Warranty
							

								Optional 10 Year Extended Warranty
							



								Year 1
							

								Lift motor burns out
							

								Manufacturer's 1st Year Full Warranty covers parts and labor
							

								Not needed, as repair was covered by Manufacturer's 1st Year Full Warranty
							



								Year 2-3
							

								The drive belt is not functioning
							

								Manufacturer covers part; consumer must pay for shipping of part and labor
							

								The manufacturer still covers the part, we order the part for you, pay the shipping, and provide installation at no charge
							



								Year 3-10
							

								Drive motor stops working
							

								Consumer must pay for part, shipping, and labor
							

								We purchase the part, pay the shipping, and provide installation at no additional charge
							



								Year 11-20
							

								Problem due to defective steel part
							

								Manufacturer covers most of part; consumer must pay remaining portion, shipping, and labor
							

								10 Year Warranty has expired, base is covered by the Manufacturer's Warranty only
							








						Need Assistance with Set Up or Old Mattress Removal?
					

					Most orders require little or no assembly, however your shipping notification email will contain information 
					for contacting several local skilled craftsman in your area who can assist with assembly or old mattress 
					removal once your order is delivered, for as little as $99. No more waiting at home for 8 hours for a 
					delivery agent. Use the local ratings and reviews we provide to find the perfect local contractor with 
					

					greater control over the services you need at the time of your choosing. 
					*In-home services provided by an independent service provider.
					





