very expensive mistake
Admittedly comfort if very subjective....but this was a very disappointing purchase. I bought bed approx 2 years ago- usually wake up in more back and hip pain than I went to bed with. The problem is that the mattress is rigid- not firm with support nor comfy with give.....somehow it manages to not be supportive yet also doesnt flex to body contours. I spent a lot of time researching because I wanted the least toxic, most environmentally friend mattress I could afford. I think the materials do meet that criteria. I did try the comfort exchange, but by the time the new layer came, I tried it, decided I didnt like it, it was too late to return. I was prompted to write this review as plush beds came up when I was internet searching for a mattress topper- to try to make bed tolerable. oh well.



