what the difference between split queen and regular queen ?



rick p



                            on May 26, 2017
                        








BEST ANSWER: A queen sized bed is one 60" x 80" bed. The adjustable bed will work as one unit where the entire head and/or foot of bed moves up and down as one unit.A split queen sized bed is (2) separate 30" x 80" beds, side by side. The split queen adjustable bed is also 2 separate beds, side by side. Each side of the adjustable bed has its own remote control and each side moves independently. Both sides can be synced together to use as one unit as well. You should order the same size mattress as the adjustable frame.

Reply

Inaccurate



            Dawn H
        

Staff
on May 29, 2017



















