LEG - Market Data & News
LEG - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

Leggett & Platt Incorporated (LEG) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 19, as the stock 
gained 0.65% to close at $52.59. On the day, Leggett & Platt Incorporated saw 1.1 million shares trade hands on 7,642 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 724,924 shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $54.97 and $44.02 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $52.19, and its 200-day SMA $49.12. Leggett & Platt Incorporated 
has a P/B ratio of 6.54. It also has a P/E ratio of 19.  


Leggett & Platt Inc is a manufacturer that conceives designs and produces engineered components and products found in homes, offices, retail stores, automobiles and commercial aircraft.

Headquartered in Carthage, MO, Leggett & Platt Incorporated has 21,000 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Karl G. Glassman.


