Leggett & Platt - Wikipedia





















 






Leggett & Platt

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
  (Redirected from Leggett & Platt Inc)

					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This article needs additional citations for verification. Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. (January 2009) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)



Leggett & Platt


Type

Public


Traded as
NYSE: LEG
S&P 500 Component


Industry
Residential Bedding and Furniture
Automotive Seating
Industrial Materials


Founded
1883; 134 years ago (1883)


Headquarters
Carthage, Missouri, United States



Key people

Karl G. Glassman, President & CEO


Revenue
$3.75 billion USD (2016)



Operating income

$522 million USD (2016)



Net income

$367 million USD (2016)



Number of employees

21,300 (2016)


Website
leggett.com


Leggett & Platt (L&P), based in Carthage, Missouri, is a diversified manufacturer (and member of the S&P 500 Index) that designs and produces various engineered components and products. The firm was founded in 1883, and consists of 17 business units, 21,000 employee-partners, and 130 manufacturing facilities located in 19 countries.[citation needed]



Contents


1 Company segments

1.1 Residential Products
1.2 Industrial Products
1.3 Furniture Products
1.4 Specialized Products


2 Leggett management
3 Board of directors
4 Company history
5 Timeline
6 Executive leadership: past & present
7 LEG stock
8 References
9 External links



Company segments[edit]
Residential Products[edit]
Leggett & Platt provides a variety of components and machinery used by bedding manufacturers in the production and assembly of their finished products. Leggett & Platt also produces and distributes carpet cushion for residential and commercial applications. In addition, they are a major distributor of geo components used in ground stabilization, drainage protection, erosion control, and weed control.[1]
Industrial Products[edit]
Leggett & Platt is a producer of drawn steel wire. The company's three wire mills produce virtually all of the wire consumed by their other domestic business, as well as supplying external customers. Much of the steel rod used to produce this wire is manufactured in Leggett & Platt's own rod mill. They also produce and distribute wire products for various industrial applications.[2]
Furniture Products[edit]
Leggett & Platt is the world's leading independent manufacturer of motion and other components for work and residential furniture. In addition, they produce select lines of private-label finished furniture. They are also a leading supplier of adjustable beds and fashion bed products, which are sold primarily to bedding retailers and other retail markets.[3]
Specialized Products[edit]
Leggett & Platt is a designer and manufacturer of automotive seating support, pneumatic and mechanical lumbar systems. They are also a supplier of titanium, nickel, and stainless steel tubing to the aerospace industry. It is a supplier of service van interiors used in commercial vehicles.
Leggett management[edit]
As of January 2017, senior corporate executives included:

Karl G. Glassman, President & CEO
Perry E. Davis, EVP & President, Residential & Industrial Products Segments
J. Mitchell Dolloff, EVP & President, Furniture & Specialized Products Segments
Matthew C. Flanigan, EVP & CFO
David M. DeSonier, SVP Strategy and Investor Relations

