Good investment, we think at 1 week
We got 2 Twin XLs to place on the Prodigy 2.0 split King adjustable bed. Excellent night sleep even on first night, though hard to sort out what part is due to the mattress and what part to the adjustable bed base. At least in theory, a purely organic bed and bed covers/sheets, etc without chemicals is attractive. Hardest part of the mattress purchase is guessing at firmness that will be best. We got 1 med & 1 med-firm - will take more time to decide if one of them should be change to the other. But after less than a week conclusion is it was a good purchase that is good for our health, our backs, and our comfort. Both the mattress & bases have long warranties so hopefully the $5-6K cost is divided over much more than a decade. At this point, we think it was a good choice.



