It's a Dream!!
After over a year of debating and research, I purchased the Scape split King with a Latex Mattress (specifically for no off-gassing).  I had to communicate with Jo several times in customer service re: timing of delivery and she was fabulous! The bed arrived in two large cardboard boxes about the size of a twin box-spring mattress. The mattresses were compressed and in tight rolls. The delivery came when I was working a 24 hour call shift (I'm Nurse-Midwife). My husband was against the purchase and washed his hands of it. He wasn't happy about the $$$ I spent on it. (My money). Anyway, I digress.  He agreed to accept the delivery but said he would have nothing to do with setting the whole thing up. For that reason I ordered the "white glove service" where they set it up for you.  Through a mix-up with our local delivery service, they were unable to set up- just deliver.  I was sweating it because I didn't want to ask my husband for help.  So, at 0500 after a stressful day of work I came home to find the delivery. EEG!! So exciting!  My husband was asleep in the guest room and I set to work.  I open the two adjustable bases. The instructions were super clear and easy. I popped on the legs and wheels. I rolled the beds over and shoved them into place. I plugged them in to test them. Perfect. I rebuilt my bed frame around the Split King Scape bases and then unrolled my latex mattresses and heaved them up on the bases...all 137 lbs of me. No problem.  I did use a 3" foam topper that we had on our previous king size mattress. I just cut it in half with scissors.  Put sheets on, showered and did what I couldn't wait to do...I fell into that bed and raised the feet up!!  My poor feet were barking from work and it was like being cradled by the hand of God!! (In fact, we refer to our bed as the HOG (Hand of God) because if feels like the heavens opened up and God stretched out His hands to cradle you to sleep! My husband came upstairs to see what the commotion was (I was being really quiet but then accidentally dropped the hammer on the hard wood floor) and saw that I had assembled everything in about an hour.  He is now in love with the bed (of course). He has used a C-Pap since he was 25 years old and finds that just a slight incline of his head helps with his sleep apnea.  Before this bed, I woke up feeling like I had been beaten with a 2x4.  I thought there was no way my body could handle being a midwife for many more years.  Now post-bed, I do NOT have those morning aches and pains. I LOVE THIS BED. I'm glad I bit the bullet and purchased one now. Highly recommend to anyone.  But, if you are a nurse, do yourself a favor and get an adjustable bed. 13 hour shifts are brutal. You deserve it!!!! 10 stars.



Was this review helpful?
